text: I like to look for those opportunities. You don't see them every day, but you do see them. You know, we have designed a number of filters over the year to kind of look for these things and where can you find them and look for some of these different relationships. And when we find them, we always go investigate very carefully to make sure, again, almost with a mindset of, I got to find a reason not to do this trade. If there's an option that I can own for some reasonable period of time in a market that has some continuity to it, there's not some reason to expect that the price six months from now and a year and a half from now are literally two different things and they're totally unrelated. Like there's always, you know, a market like gas has big seasonal swings and the fundamentals can certainly shift over any kind of six or 12 month period, but the whole curve still does move together a lot. And there's still a lot of correlation embedded in some of these things. And so finding those opportunities, we try very, very hard to find those things where we can own convexity and not only not pay a lot, but sometimes get paid a little bit to carry it.
